cted everything needed, but I'm not sure. I should consider scanning for skills, though nothing seems clear right now—self-improvement might be the only thing. Hmm, perhaps reviewing the README could help clarify things. I'll plan to read it first, then move on to execution.\"}]}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kyk9BSXWJLQPb0Sp9IP1vZDK|fc_037a9d61271453910169ca73de9b8c8194b2c098886812e36b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\task_watchdog\\README.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\task_watchdog\\\\README.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":9662,"output":80,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12302,"cost":{"input":0.024155000000000003,"output":0.0012000000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0006399999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.025995000000000004}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774875607939,"responseId":"resp_037a9d61271453910169ca73d916d0819483f0ed7bec4f2ae8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f52e618d","parentId":"a7211e3a","timestamp":"2026-03-30T13:00:15.747Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_kyk9BSXWJLQPb0Sp9IP1vZDK|fc_037a9d61271453910169ca73de9b8c8194b2c098886812e36b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Task Watchdog\n\nGlobal task registry + watchdog for Tobias long-running tasks.\n\n## Goal\n- track tasks launched by Tobias\n- check every 5 minutes\n- notify Lucca every 10 minutes while running\n- send final notification on completion/failure\n- stay silent when no tasks are active\n\n## Files\n- `config.json` — watchdog settings\n- `active_tasks.json` — active monitored tasks\n- `task_history.jsonl` — completed/failed task history\n- `watchdog.py` — deterministic status checker\n\n## Scope (MVP)\n- monitors Tobias-launched subagents first\n- stores global registry so it can work across chats/surfaces\n- internal timestamps are ISO; user-facing messages must be human formatted\n\n## Operational protocol (mandatory)\nFor every long-running subagent launched by Tobias:\n1. spawn the subagent\n2. immediately register it in `active_tasks.json`\n3. only after registration, confirm to Lucca that the task was launched\n\nRule:\n- spawn without register = incomplete launch\n- do not claim a task is being monitored unless it is already in the registry\n\n## Safety layers\nThe watchdog design uses three layers together:\n1. **Launch wrapper discipline** — spawn -> register -> confirm\n2. **No-confirmation-without-registry** — Tobias must not claim monitoring without persisted registration\n3. **Launch audit** — `watchdog_launch_audit.py` scans for recent unregistered subagent sessions and auto-registers them as a fallback safety net\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774875615712}}
